        "title": "Problems returning the length of the longest String among the values of input in a HashMap",
        "body": "<p>I've written a method named q1 that takes a <code>HashMap&lt;String, String&gt;<\/code> and returns the longest String among the HashMap values.<\/p>\n\n<p>This is the code I've written. I'm not sure why it's not working.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int q1(HashMap&lt;String, String&gt;name) {\n\n    String longest = \"\";\n\n    for (String key : name.keySet()) {\n       if( name.size() &gt; longest.length() )\n       {\n          longest = key;\n\n       }\n\n   }\n    int sized = longest.length();\n   return sized;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This is my code after I edited it: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int q1(HashMap&lt;String ,String  &gt;name) {\n\n    String longest = \"\";\n\n    for (String key : name.values()) {\n       if(name.get(key).length() &gt; longest.length() )\n       {\n          longest = key;\n\n       }\n\n   }\n    int sized = longest.length();\n   return sized;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Im still getting this error:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>correct\":false,\"feedback\":\"(class java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException)\nError while attempting to call static method q1(HashMap) on input\n[{\\\"basically\\\":\\\"FIFTY\\\",\\\"frozen\\\":\\\"LivEr\\\",\\\"combination\\\":\\\"ColONiAl\\\",\\\"liquid\\\":\\\"deAR\\\",\\\"custody\\\":\\\"OPPortuNITY\\\",\\\"buck\\\":\\\"bLADE\\\",\\\"surprisingly\\\":\\\"STaGe\\\"}]\\nVerify that you can call q1 from your main method without error\"}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
