            "creation_date": 1520965392,
            "body": "<p>You're getting the length of the key, not the value. You need to use:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>name.get(key).length()\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>instead of<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>name.size()\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>also note that the way to get the length of a String in Java is <code>.length()<\/code>, not <code>.size()<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 49263288,
            "question_id": 49263227
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/10155291083857568/picture?type=large",
